Interface IDContainer<E extends AgenaRiskException>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of AgenaRiskException thrown on error
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Model, Network

    public interface IDContainer<E extends AgenaRiskException>
    Classes that have a collection of some identifiable objects that have a unique ID should implement this.

      • changeContainedId

        @Deprecated
default <I extends Identifiable> boolean changeContainedId(I identifiable,
                                                                        java.lang.String id)
                                                                 throws E extends AgenaRiskException
        Deprecated. For internal use only. You will break referential integrity by using this method directly.
        Changes the ID of the Identifiable in some mapped reference of the IDContainer.
        Does not actually modify Identifiable, which should be done externally.
        Type Parameters:
        I - Type of the identifiable object
        Parameters:
        identifiable - the object which ID needs updating
        id - new ID
        Returns:
        true if ID was changed and false if Identifiable is not contained in the map
        Throws:
        E - if ID already taken
        E extends AgenaRiskException
